  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "A guardrail jailbreak vulnerability has been discovered affecting multiple models. The specific flaw manifests when attackers introduce random spacing within a prompt, effectively disrupting how the model tokenizes the input. By splitting words like \"Chemicals\" into parts such as \"chem-\", \"ic-\", and \"al,\" the technique circumvents the model's primary content filter classifiers, which typically flag restricted phrases or tokens. This token manipulation allows attackers to bypass inference restrictions around providing information hazards and violating laws."
  },
